ea, 74, Dies; Anthropologist Wrote About Jewish Culture\"</a>. <i>washingtonpost.com</i>. 7 April 2009.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=washingtonpost.com&amp;rft.atitle=Ruth+Fredman+Cernea%2C+74%2C+Dies%3B+Anthropologist+Wrote+About+Jewish+Culture&amp;rft.date=2009-04-07&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fwp-dyn%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2F2009%2F04%2F06%2FAR2009040603464.html%3Fhpid%3Dsec-religion&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARuth+Cernea\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Cernea, Ruth Fredman (24 November 2006). <i>Almost Englishmen: Baghdadi Jews in British Burma</i>. Lexington Books. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0739116479\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0739116479\">0739116479</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Almost+Englishmen%3A+Baghdadi+Jews+in+British+Burma&amp;rft.pub=Lexington+Books&amp;rft.date=2006-11-24&amp;rft.isbn=0739116479&amp;rft.aulast=Cernea&amp;rft.aufirst=Ruth+Fredman&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARuth+Cernea\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Cohen, Ted (1 December 2006).  Cernea, Ruth Fredman, ed. <i>The Great Latke-Hamantash Debate</i>. University Of Chicago Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"